    {
      "title": "The financial blind spot that gets product managers fired",
      "url": "https://www.productcoalition.com/p/the-number-your-board-asks-first",
      "source": "Product Coalition",
      "type": "article",
      "date": "2026-04-10T14:13:40+00:00",
      "summary": "Many product managers excel at product metrics like NPS and activation rates but are dangerously unaware of the financial metrics boards actually care about — particularly LTV-to-CAC ratio and payback period. The author argues this blind spot is one of the leading reasons experienced PMs get cut in budget reviews. PMs who want to be taken seriously at the executive level need to own their product's financial narrative.",
      "tags": [
        "Metrics",
        "Stakeholders",
        "Product Finance"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Commercial vs Internal Products",
      "url": "https://www.svpg.com/commercial-vs-internal-products/",
      "source": "SVPG",
      "type": "article",
      "date": "2026-04-09T19:52:26+00:00",
      "summary": "Marty Cagan examines the fundamental differences between building commercial products for paying customers and internal tools for employees, arguing that the constraints, incentives, and success metrics are so different they require distinct PM skill sets. Internal products often lack the forcing function of market competition, which leads to lower quality and slower iteration. A useful framework for PMs transitioning between these contexts.",
