      "date": "2025-12-19T12:32:20+00:00",
      "summary": "Marty Cagan examines how Google's product model has evolved over the years, distinguishing between the early innovation-driven culture and the more process-heavy approach that emerged as the company scaled. He argues that Google's struggles with product innovation in recent years stem from moving away from empowered product teams toward a feature-factory model. A useful diagnostic for PMs assessing their own organisation's product culture.",
