      "url": "https://www.ben-evans.com/benedictevans/2025/6/9/generative-ais-metrics-question",
      "source": "Benedict Evans",
      "type": "trend",
      "date": "2025-06-09T13:15:31+00:00",
      "summary": "Benedict Evans draws parallels between the early internet's metric confusion — hits, registered users, MAU — and the current struggle to measure meaningful AI adoption. He argues that metrics like weekly active users obscure whether AI is genuinely changing behaviour, and that the industry needs better proxies for real value creation. PMs building AI features should think carefully about what success actually looks like beyond surface-level engagement metrics.",
